article.description: Kenny Aninye scored 15 points as Stetson defeated Jacksonville 64-59 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Aninye scores 15 points as Stetson holds off Jacksonville
article.linkText: Aninye scores 15 points as Stetson holds off Jacksonville
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Kenny Aninye scored 15 points as Stetson defeated Jacksonville 64-59 on Saturday night. Rob Perry had 13 points for Stetson (9-11, 3-2 Atlantic Sun Conference), which has won four straight on the road. Mahamadou Diawara added 11 points, nine rebounds and three blocks. Joel Kabimba had 10 points and nine rebounds. Aamahne Santos had 13 points for the Dolphins (8-12, 1-4). Destin Barnes added 11 points. David Bell had 5 points and 15 rebounds. Stetson takes on NJIT at home on Thursday. Jacksonville faces Lipscomb on the road on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
